T3 (Fig. 
4E
) a cleaning limb. First segment with two long apical setae (dp and d2) and one shorter medio-ventral seta (d1). Second segment fused with third segment, with e-seta of medium length, and with f-seta reaching tip of segment. Distal part of limb consisting of a pincer-organ (fusion between tip of third segment and fourth segment), bearing a seta (h3) of medium length and a short, serrated seta (h2); h3 ~ 2/3 of the length of penultimate segment, h2 ~ 1/3 of length of h3.

CR (Fig. 
4C
